Description:
Ballistics of 115x728R 3UBM5 round, with the 3BM6 steel core APFSDS-T shot, fired from the U-5TS tank gun (GRAU index 2A20), chiefly employed on the T-62 tank. Introduction date is some point from 1964 to 1966, with the round revised in 1966-1968 to eliminate the armor-piercing cap. Modelling based on the following information:

Barrel Length:      5840 mm
Cartridge Length:    723 mm
Projectile Mass:   5.335 kg (measured, Chinese)
                    5.34 kg (authorized, Soviet)
Projectile Travel:  5117 mm  (estimated from above)
Peak Pressure:      3650 kgf/cm² breech, copper crusher gauge (1.12 x 0.09805).
Muzzle Velocity:    1600 m/s 
Chambrage:          1.37     from 枪炮内弹道学 (2014).
Propellant:        7.934 kg (measured, Chinese), 
                     8.1 kg (authorized, Soviet)

Mass      Propellant  Geometry   Web   ⌀Perf Len   Force (from "545")
                                 mm    mm    mm    kgf-dm/kg
1.1   kg  Pyroxylin   18/1-37.5  1.73  1.89  375    830,000 
2.1   kg  Pyroxylin   18/1-28.5  1.73  1.88  285    830,000 kgf-dm/kg
4.734 kg  Pyroxylin   12/7       1.27  0.44  13.67  900,000 kgf-dm/kg

Force value from Chinese chemical analysis of captured example (vehicle T-62 №545). Authorized load is 8.1 kg from Soviet manual.
